[{"id":"FT1987","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"A graph of f(x) is drawn on an unscaled y-axis.  The graph of f has x-intercepts at -3, some unspecified x value between -3 and 0, the origin and 3.  The graph begins at a point in the second quadrant to the left of x = -3 and decreases, concave up to some minimum point in the third quadrant.  The graph is then increasing and concave up until it reaches the x-axis, at which point, the graph continues to increase but is concave down until it reaches a maximum point in the second quadrant.  From this point, the graph is decreasing and concave down, passing through the origin, after which it continues to decrease, but is concave up, until it reaches some minimum point in the fourth quadrant.  The graph then is increasing and concave up until it reaches the x-intercept at x = 3, after which the graph continues to increase, but is concave down, until the end of the interval.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/a7f2a195565ddf6066e370c05409770f/original.png\" /></p>\n\n<p>The regions <em>A</em>, <em>B</em>, and <em>C</em> in the figure above are bounded by the graph of the function <em>f</em> and the <em>x</em>-axis. If the area of each region is 2, what is the value of <span aria-label=\"the integral from negative 3 to 3 of open paren f of x plus 1 close paren times d x\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo>∫</mo> <mrow> <mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn> </mrow> <mn>3</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <mrow><mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo></mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mstyle><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@43C6@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>?</p>\n","choicesHtml":["<p>-2</p>","<p>-1</p>","<p>4</p>","<p>7</p>","<p>12</p>"],"answer":1}]